item.title: JDK download help!
item.dc:creator: @Sonis Sonis
item.description:
@Sonis wrote:

http://cds.sun.com/is-bin/INTERSHOP.enfinity/WFS/CDS-CDS_Developer-Site/en_US/-/USD/VerifyItem-Start/jdk-6u12-windows-i586-p.exe?BundledLineItemUUID=4fZIBe.l0HgAAAEfuPhEAdZU&OrderID=kcNIBe.lQJIAAAEfqfhEAdZU&ProductID=ZsNIBe.pM7cAAAEexzlTv_an&FileName=/jdk-6u12-windows-i586-p.exe

if that’s no longer valid try this link and jump through…
http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp

It’s the second from the top Orange download button that is located at 675,500 on the page, when screen res is at : 1280x1024. On the next screen select Windows (not windows Intel Itanium or windows x64) as you’re probably on 32bit XP. click on the I accept terms check box then click continue. You’ll then see a check mark; DO NOT CLICK IT… click on a link that’s tabbed out an inch on the under-below line. That’ll directly download the executable and not download a manager to be used to download what you want. you don’t need help installing; right? some times I can’t find downloads too, other day I couldn’t find the java3d library at sun.com/java.com… but i did find it on google >_<
